author: dlr
msg: A follow-up to r25486 simplifying the implementation of the new
svn_cl__check_boolean_prop_val() function, and adjusting an existing
test to trigger a warning to be output when Subversion think you're
attempting to unset a boolean property value.
This introduces a slight behavioral change, where empty strings like
"      " now equate to unsetting a boolean property value for purposes
of triggering a warning.  (They still set the value, however.)
accept an expected_error list, and pass this list on to
svntest.main.run_svn().  When invoking set_prop() for the
"svn:executable" property with a value that equates to "unset",
allow the command-line binary to issue a warning.
